  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An ecosystem is a community of living organisms together with the nonliving components of their environment — water, soil, atmosphere, sunlight — interacting as a system. The term was coined by Arthur Tansley in 1935. Ecosystems can be as small as a tide pool or as large as the Amazon basin, but the concept is the same: organisms and their physical environment, connected by flows of energy and cycles of matter.\n",
